   abstract = {The majority of mobile devices today are based on Arm architecture that supports the hosting of trusted applications in Trusted Execution Environment (TEE). RISC-V is a relatively new open-source instruction set architecture that was engineered to ﬁt many uses. In one potential RISC-V usage scenario, mobile devices could be based on RISC-V hardware.},
